title.narrative: Output 6.3: Strengthened political commitment, accountability and national capacity to legislate, plan and budget for scaling up quality rights- and gender-sensitive child protection services for vulnerable children and their families.

description.narrative: UNICEF has contributed to strengthened commitment in Government towards legal reform, strategic planning and budgeting for child protection interventions in the justice, law enforcement and welfare sectors. UNICEF support helped produce draft laws, legal submissions, strategic plans and budget advocacy and position papers to promote dialogue to move the child protection agenda towards more protective outcomes for children in Zimbabwe. Zimbabwe's commitment to address violence against children culminated in the country's accession to the Global Partnership to End Violence against children, acquiring pathfinder status in October 2019 that was publicly announced during the CRC@30 celebrations. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
